cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the recognition of named entities in Web and Blogosphere data, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of Semantic Web resources, which falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL) and semantic web (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of cultural and technological changes on language, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computers and society (cs.CY).
